{
  "summary": "This change deletes the production RDS PostgreSQL instance prod-db, which serves as the primary data store for the entire application stack.\n\n**Highest Risk: API Lambda Functions (Score: 90/100, Critical)**\nThree Lambda functions (user-api, order-api, payment-api) connect directly to this database. Deleting the RDS instance will cause immediate connection failures, resulting in 500 errors on all API endpoints. There is no failover — these functions have the database connection string hardcoded in their environment variables. Suggested mitigation: This deletion should not proceed without first migrating all data to a replacement instance and updating all Lambda environment variables.\n\n**Critical Risk: ECS Order Processing Service (Score: 88/100, Critical)**\nThe order-processing ECS service writes transaction records to this database. Deletion will cause order processing to halt, potentially losing in-flight transactions. Suggested mitigation: Drain the order queue and ensure all pending transactions are committed before any database changes.\n\n**Critical Risk: API Gateway (Score: 85/100, Critical)**\nThe API Gateway routes to the Lambda functions that depend on this database. While the gateway itself won't fail, every request it routes will return errors, effectively making the entire public API non-functional. Suggested mitigation: Implement a maintenance mode response at the API Gateway level before proceeding.\n\nOverall, deleting this database will cause a complete production outage affecting all 8 downstream services. This is a catastrophic change that should only proceed as part of a planned migration with a fully tested replacement database already serving traffic.",
